### API LAYER 1: Azure AI Capacity API

**Purpose:** Show real-time available GPU capacity per model / region / deployment type.

```javascript
/* === REAL API: Azure AI Capacity API ===
 * Endpoint: GET https://management.azure.com/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}
 *           /providers/Microsoft.CognitiveServices/locations/{location}
 *           /models?api-version=2024-10-01
 *
 * Auth: Bearer token via Azure AD (scope: https://management.azure.com/.default)
 *       Use MSAL.js or DefaultAzureCredential in production.
 *
 * Key response fields:
 *   - model.name                    → e.g. "gpt-4o-mini"
 *   - model.skuName                 → e.g. "GlobalProvisionedManaged"
 *   - model.availableCapacity       → PTU units available to allocate
 *   - model.deploymentTypes[]       → ["GlobalStandard", "GlobalProvisionedManaged", "DataZone", "Regional"]
 *   - location                      → Azure region, e.g. "eastus", "westus", "swedencentral"
 *
 * Required params:
 *   subscriptionId  → from Azure Portal > Subscriptions
 *   location        → target region
 *   api-version     → "2024-10-01" (latest stable)
 *
 * async function fetchCapacity(subscriptionId, location, bearerToken) {
 *   const url = `https://management.azure.com/subscriptions/${subscriptionId}
 *                /providers/Microsoft.CognitiveServices/locations/${location}
 *                /models?api-version=2024-10-01`;
 *   const res = await fetch(url, {
 *     headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${bearerToken}` }
 *   });
 *   const data = await res.json();
 *   return data.value; // array of model capacity objects
 * }
 * === END REAL API === */
```

