### API LAYER 2: Azure Monitor Metrics API

**Purpose:** Pull real-time and historical usage — Input TPM, Output TPM, cache hit rate, throttling.

```javascript
/* === REAL API: Azure Monitor Metrics API ===
 * Endpoint: GET https://management.azure.com/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}
 *           /resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}
 *           /providers/Microsoft.CognitiveServices/accounts/{accountName}
 *           /providers/microsoft.insights/metrics
 *           ?api-version=2023-10-01
 *           &metricnames=TokenTransaction,CacheHitRate,BlockedCalls,SuccessfulCalls
 *           &timespan=PT1H
 *           &interval=PT1M
 *           &aggregation=Total,Average
 *
 * Auth: Bearer token (same scope as above)
 *
 * Required params:
 *   subscriptionId    → Azure subscription ID (GUID)
 *   resourceGroupName → Resource group containing the OpenAI resource
 *   accountName       → Azure OpenAI resource name (e.g. "myopenai-eastus")
 *
 * Key metric names for Foundry/OpenAI:
 *   "TokenTransaction"          → Input + output tokens (split by dimension "TokenType": prompt / completion)
 *   "ProcessedPromptTokens"     → Prompt (input) tokens only
 *   "GeneratedCompletionTokens" → Completion (output) tokens only
 *   "CacheMatchRate"            → Prompt cache hit rate (0.0–1.0)
 *   "BlockedCalls"              → Throttled (429) requests
 *   "SuccessfulCalls"           → 200 OK requests
 *   "ServerErrors"              → 500-level errors
 *
 * Note: subscriptionId alone is NOT sufficient — you must also provide
 *   resourceGroupName + accountName (the full resource ARM path) to scope
 *   metrics to a specific Azure OpenAI resource.
 *
 * async function fetchMonitorMetrics(subscriptionId, resourceGroup, accountName, bearerToken) {
 *   const resourcePath = `/subscriptions/${subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/${resourceGroup}`
 *     + `/providers/Microsoft.CognitiveServices/accounts/${accountName}`;
 *   const url = `https://management.azure.com${resourcePath}`
 *     + `/providers/microsoft.insights/metrics`
 *     + `?api-version=2023-10-01`
 *     + `&metricnames=ProcessedPromptTokens,GeneratedCompletionTokens,CacheMatchRate,BlockedCalls,SuccessfulCalls`
 *     + `&timespan=PT1H&interval=PT1M&aggregation=Total,Average`;
 *   const res = await fetch(url, {
 *     headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${bearerToken}` }
 *   });
 *   return await res.json();
 * }
 * === END REAL API === */
```

