### API LAYER 3: Azure AI Foundry Quota API

**Purpose:** Show subscription-level quota allocation vs. usage per model, deployment type, region. Show rate limit headroom.

```javascript
/* === REAL API: Azure AI Foundry Quota API ===
 * Endpoint: GET https://management.azure.com/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}
 *           /providers/Microsoft.CognitiveServices/locations/{location}
 *           /usages?api-version=2024-10-01
 *
 * Also (for deployment-level quota):
 *   GET https://management.azure.com/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}
 *       /resourceGroups/{resourceGroup}
 *       /providers/Microsoft.CognitiveServices/accounts/{accountName}
 *       /deployments?api-version=2024-10-01
 *
 * Auth: Bearer token (same scope)
 *
 * Key response fields from /usages:
 *   - name.value             → quota type, e.g. "OpenAI.Standard.gpt-4o-mini"
 *   - currentValue           → PTUs or TPM currently allocated
 *   - limit                  → max PTUs or TPM available to this subscription
 *   - unit                   → "Count" (for PTUs) or "K" (for TPM × 1000)
 *
 * Key response fields from /deployments:
 *   - name                   → deployment name (user-defined)
 *   - properties.model.name  → model name
 *   - properties.sku.name    → "GlobalProvisionedManaged" | "GlobalStandard" etc.
 *   - properties.sku.capacity→ allocated PTUs (for PTU deployments)
 *   - properties.rateLimits  → array of { key: "token", count: N, renewalPeriod: 60 }
 *
 * async function fetchQuota(subscriptionId, location, bearerToken) {
 *   const url = `https://management.azure.com/subscriptions/${subscriptionId}`
 *     + `/providers/Microsoft.CognitiveServices/locations/${location}`
 *     + `/usages?api-version=2024-10-01`;
 *   const res = await fetch(url, {
 *     headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${bearerToken}` }
 *   });
 *   return await res.json();
 * }
 * === END REAL API === */
```

